{
  "text": "Let's create a transit gateway and attach multiple VPCs to it. We create the transit gateway first, then create attachments for each VPC. Each attachment connects a VPC subnet to the transit gateway. We create route tables in the transit gateway to control which attachments can communicate. By default, attachments in the same route table can communicate with each other. We also add routes in each VPC's route tables to send traffic destined for other VPCs to the transit gateway. This creates a fully connected network where for all VPCs to communicate with each other, the VPCs can communicate with each other.",
